OL,3,CEl Nino officially declared but what
OL,4,Cdoes it mean for UK weather?
OL,6,FEl Nino has been formally declared by
OL,7,Fthe US weather agency, the National
OL,8,FOceanic and Atmospheric Administration
OL,9,F(NOAA), and it's forecast to be
OL,10,Fstronger than ever.
OL,12,FThe phenomenon is formed thousands of
OL,13,Fmiles away in the Pacific, and in the
OL,14,Fsimplest terms, it causes the winds
OL,15,Fthat move across the ocean to weaken
OL,16,For even change direction.
OL,26,@kD@FTwnD@FTw
