OL,3,CEl Nino officially declared but what
OL,4,Cdoes it mean for UK weather?
OL,6,FThe UK is thousands of miles away, and
OL,7,Four weather is directly influenced by
OL,8,Fthe North Atlantic Ocean, the Jet
OL,9,FStream and atmospheric patterns
OL,10,Fconnected to the Atlantic.
OL,12,FIf and when El Nino's influence
OL,13,Freaches Europe, it has to interact
OL,14,Fwith complex chains of atmospheric
OL,15,Fscenarios - making its effect weaker
OL,16,Fand less reliable in the UK.
OL,18,FWhat does this mean?
OL,26,@kD@FTwtD@RTw
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/7
